{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VqKsLNuQnuZKkfpgsmTQ3f","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 14.3: Docker Pre-check and Orphan Cleanup\n     2→\n     3→Status: review\n     4→\n     5→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     6→\n     7→## Story\n     8→\n     9→As a developer running harness-run,\n    10→I want Docker availability checked BEFORE any verification attempt and orphaned containers cleaned up automatically,\n    11→So that sessions don't burn 30 minutes on Docker failures and leftover containers don't interfere with fresh runs.\n    12→\n    13→## Acceptance Criteria\n    14→\n    15→1. Given Docker daemon is not running, when `codeharness run` executes its pre-flight checks, then it exits with a non-zero code and outputs `[FAIL] Docker not available` before spawning the agent <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→2. Given Docker daemon is not running, when `codeharness run` executes its pre-flight checks, then no agent process is spawned (no Ralph/Claude invocation occurs) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→3. Given a leftover `codeharness-verify-*` container (exited or dead) from a crashed session, when `codeharness run` pre-flight runs, then the orphaned container is removed and an `[INFO]` message is logged <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→4. Given leftover `codeharness-shared-*` and `codeharness-collector-*` containers (exited or dead), when `codeharness run` pre-flight runs, then those orphaned containers are also removed <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→5. Given Docker is available but no orphaned containers exist, when `codeharness run` pre-flight runs, then cleanup completes silently (no error, no unnecessary output) and execution continues normally <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→6. Given Docker is available and orphan cleanup encounters a removal failure on one container, when pre-flight runs, then it continues removing other containers and does not abort the session <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21→7. Given `npm run build` runs after all changes, then TypeScript compilation succeeds with zero errors <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22→8. Given `npm test` runs after all changes, then all existing tests pass with zero regressions <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    23→9. Given no new file created for this story, when line count is checked, then no modified file exceeds 300 lines <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    24→\n    25→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    26→\n    27→- [x] Task 1 (AC: 1, 2): Add Docker pre-check to `run.ts` pre-flight section\n    28→  - [x] After state reconciliation (step 1b) and before story count check (step 2), call `isDockerAvailable()` from `src/lib/docker/index.js`\n    29→  - [x] If false, call `fail('[FAIL] Docker not available — install Docker or start the daemon')`, set `process.exitCode = 1`, and return early\n    30→  - [x] This prevents any agent spawn, prompt generation, or Docker operations from executing\n    31→\n    32→- [x] Task 2 (AC: 3, 4): Consolidate orphan cleanup in `container-cleanup.ts`\n    33→  - [x] Extend `STALE_PATTERNS` array to include `'codeharness-verify-'` alongside existing `'codeharness-shared-'` and `'codeharness-collector-'`\n    34→  - [x] This single change makes the existing `cleanupContainers()` function also clean up verify containers\n    35→  - [x] No new function needed — the existing logic already handles Docker-not-available, per-container failure resilience, and Result<CleanupResult> return\n    36→\n    37→- [x] Task 3 (AC: 3, 4, 5): Call cleanup from `run.ts` pre-flight\n    38→  - [x] After the Docker pre-check passes, call `cleanupContainers()` from `src/modules/infra/index.js`\n    39→  - [x] If result is success and `containersRemoved > 0`, log `[INFO] Cleaned up ${n} orphaned container(s): ${names.join(', ')}`\n    40→  - [x] If result is failure, log `[WARN] Container cleanup failed: ${error}` but do NOT abort the session\n    41→\n    42→- [x] Task 4 (AC: 3): Update `src/lib/docker/cleanup.ts` stub to delegate to infra module\n    43→  - [x] Replace the placeholder `cleanupOrphanedContainers()` with a real implementation that calls `cleanupContainers()` from the infra module\n    44→  - [x] Or leave as-is if it's acceptable to keep the stub (the run.ts pre-flight calls the infra module directly)\n    45→\n    46→- [x] Task 5 (AC: 1, 2, 5, 6): Add unit tests for pre-flight Docker check and cleanup in run.ts\n    47→  - [x] Test: Docker not available -> fail message, exitCode 1, no agent spawn\n    48→  - [x] Test: Docker available, no orphans -> continues normally\n    49→  - [x] Test: Docker available, orphans found -> cleanup runs, info logged, continues\n    50→  - [x] Test: Docker available, cleanup fails -> warning logged, continues\n    51→\n    52→- [x] Task 6 (AC: 3, 4): Add test for verify-pattern inclusion in container-cleanup.ts\n    53→  - [x] Test: stale `codeharness-verify-*` containers are found and removed\n    54→  - [x] Extend existing tests in `src/modules/infra/__tests__/container-cleanup.test.ts`\n    55→\n    56→- [x] Task 7 (AC: 7): Run `npm run build` — TypeScript compilation succeeds\n    57→- [x] Task 8 (AC: 8): Run `npm test` — all existing tests pass, zero regressions\n    58→- [x] Task 9 (AC: 9): Verify all modified files are under 300 lines\n    59→\n    60→## Dev Notes\n    61→\n    62→### Architecture Compliance\n    63→\n    64→- **Decision 11 (Process Enforcement):** This story implements two of five embedded gates in harness-run Step 1 pre-flight: Docker pre-check and orphan cleanup. The architecture specifies `docker info` as the check, but `isDockerAvailable()` already exists in `src/lib/docker/health.ts` and uses `docker --version` with a 10s timeout — use it.\n    65→- **Decision 7 (300-line limit, NFR5):** All modified files must stay under 300 lines. `run.ts` is currently 287 lines — budget is tight. The pre-flight additions should be ~15 lines max.\n    66→\n    67→### Implementation Guidance\n    68→\n    69→#### Where to modify\n    70→\n    71→**`src/commands/run.ts`** — The pre-flight section. Currently the file has:\n    72→- Step 1: Plugin directory check (lines 88-94)\n    73→- Step 1b: State reconciliation (lines 96-104)\n    74→- Step 2: Read sprint status for story count (lines 106-116)\n    75→\n    76→Insert Docker pre-check between step 1b and step 2. Insert orphan cleanup immediately after Docker pre-check.\n    77→\n    78→```typescript\n    79→// 1c. Docker pre-flight: fail fast if Docker unavailable\n    80→if (!isDockerAvailable()) {\n    81→  fail('[FAIL] Docker not available — install Docker or start the daemon', outputOpts);\n    82→  process.exitCode = 1;\n    83→  return;\n    84→}\n    85→\n    86→// 1d. Orphan container cleanup (best-effort — failures warn but don't abort)\n    87→const cleanup = cleanupContainers();\n    88→if (cleanup.success && cleanup.data.containersRemoved > 0) {\n    89→  info(`[INFO] Cleaned up ${cleanup.data.containersRemoved} orphaned container(s): ${cleanup.data.names.join(', ')}`, outputOpts);\n    90→} else if (!cleanup.success) {\n    91→  info(`[WARN] Container cleanup failed: ${cleanup.error}`, outputOpts);\n    92→}\n    93→```\n    94→\n    95→This adds ~10 lines to run.ts (287 -> ~297, under 300).\n    96→\n    97→**`src/modules/infra/container-cleanup.ts`** — Add `'codeharness-verify-'` to `STALE_PATTERNS`:\n    98→\n    99→```typescript\n   100→const STALE_PATTERNS = ['codeharness-shared-', 'codeharness-collector-', 'codeharness-verify-'];\n   101→```\n   102→\n   103→This is a 0-line-count change (just extending the array literal). The file is currently 84 lines.\n   104→\n   105→#### Imports needed in run.ts\n   106→\n   107→```typescript\n   108→import { isDockerAvailable } from '../lib/docker/index.js';\n   109→import { cleanupContainers } from '../modules/infra/index.js';\n   110→```\n   111→\n   112→Both modules are already used elsewhere in the codebase.\n   113→\n   114→#### What NOT to do\n   115→\n   116→- Do NOT create a new `DockerNotAvailableError` class — the old skeleton suggested this but it's unnecessary. The `fail()` output function plus early return is the established pattern in `run.ts` (see plugin directory check at line 91).\n   117→- Do NOT use `execSync('docker info')` directly — use the existing `isDockerAvailable()` from `src/lib/docker/health.ts` which already handles timeouts and error catching.\n   118→- Do NOT create a new cleanup function — the existing `cleanupContainers()` in `src/modules/infra/container-cleanup.ts` already does exactly what's needed; just extend its pattern list.\n   119→- Do NOT modify `src/modules/verify/env.ts` — it has its own `cleanupStaleContainers()` for verify-specific cleanup. The pre-flight cleanup in run.ts catches the same containers at session start. The verify module's function is used during active verification sessions. Both can coexist.\n   120→\n   121→### Testing Guidance\n   122→\n   123→- **Vitest** (not Jest). Use `vi.fn()`, `vi.mock()`, `vi.mocked()`.\n   124→- Imports: `import { describe, it, expect, vi } from 'vitest'`\n   125→- For `run.ts` tests: mock `isDockerAvailable` and `cleanupContainers` at the module level. The existing test file is at `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts`.\n   126→- For `container-cleanup.ts` tests: the existing test file at `src/modules/infra/__tests__/container-cleanup.test.ts` already has the pattern. Add one test case for `codeharness-verify-*` containers being matched.\n   127→- Follow the existing mock patterns in the test files. Both test files already mock `node:child_process` and the docker module.\n   128→\n   129→### Previous Story Intelligence (14-2)\n   130→\n   131→- Story 14-2 was a minimal change (3-line sort modification in selector.ts, ~80 lines of tests). Clean implementation.\n   132→- The 300-line limit was carefully monitored: `selector.test.ts` reached 292 lines.\n   133→- Pattern: keep implementation changes minimal, put testing effort into edge cases.\n   134→- `run.ts` is already at 287 lines — any addition MUST be lean. The ~10 lines of Docker pre-check + cleanup fit within budget but leave almost no margin.\n   135→\n   136→### Key Observations About Existing Code\n   137→\n   138→1. **`isDockerAvailable()`** (health.ts:31-38) — already exists, returns boolean, uses `docker --version` with 10s timeout. Perfect for pre-check.\n   139→2. **`cleanupContainers()`** (container-cleanup.ts:25-84) — returns `Result<CleanupResult>`, handles Docker-not-available gracefully, catches per-container failures. Only needs the verify pattern added to `STALE_PATTERNS`.\n   140→3. **`cleanupStaleContainers()`** (verify/env.ts:212-227) — a separate function that does the same thing for `codeharness-verify-*` containers during active verification. It's called from `verify-env cleanup` command. The pre-flight cleanup in run.ts covers the same containers at session start, but having both is fine (idempotent).\n   141→4. **`cleanupOrphanedContainers()`** (docker/cleanup.ts:15-22) — a stub that always returns 0. Can be left as-is or updated to delegate to the infra module. Low priority.\n   142→5. **`run.ts` structure** — sequential steps with early returns on failure. The pre-flight section (steps 1-1b) uses `fail()` + `process.exitCode = 1` + `return` pattern consistently.\n   143→6. **State reconciliation** (run.ts:96-104) — already exists as step 1b, implementing another Decision 11 gate. Docker pre-check should follow the same best-effort pattern for cleanup (warn but don't abort).\n   144→\n   145→### References\n   146→\n   147→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v3.md lines 506-520] — Decision 11: Process Enforcement\n   148→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-architecture-v3.md lines 349-363] — Story 14-3 epic definition\n   149→- [Source: src/commands/run.ts] — Run command with pre-flight section to extend\n   150→- [Source: src/modules/infra/container-cleanup.ts] — Existing cleanup function to extend with verify pattern\n   151→- [Source: src/lib/docker/health.ts lines 31-38] — `isDockerAvailable()` function to use\n   152→- [Source: src/modules/verify/env.ts lines 212-227] — Separate verify-specific cleanup (do NOT modify)\n   153→\n   154→## Files to Change\n   155→\n   156→- `src/commands/run.ts` — Add Docker pre-check (step 1c) and orphan cleanup (step 1d) to pre-flight section. +2 imports, +10 lines of logic. Target: ~297 lines (under 300).\n   157→- `src/modules/infra/container-cleanup.ts` — Add `'codeharness-verify-'` to `STALE_PATTERNS` array. 0 net lines added.\n   158→- `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` — Add tests for Docker pre-check failure and cleanup behavior.\n   159→- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/container-cleanup.test.ts` — Add test for verify-pattern container cleanup.\n   160→- `src/modules/infra/AGENTS.md` — Update container-cleanup.ts description to mention `codeharness-verify-*` pattern.\n   161→- `src/commands/AGENTS.md` — Update run.ts description to mention Docker pre-check and orphan cleanup pre-flight gates.\n   162→\n   163→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   164→## Verification Requirements\n   165→\n   166→- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/14-3-docker-precheck-orphan-cleanup.proof.md`)\n   167→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n   168→- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n   169→\n   170→## Documentation Requirements\n   171→\n   172→- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (list modules touched)\n   173→- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/14-3-docker-precheck-orphan-cleanup.md`\n   174→\n   175→## Testing Requirements\n   176→\n   177→- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   178→- [ ] Integration tests for cross-module interactions\n   179→- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n   180→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   181→\n   182→## Dev Agent Record\n   183→\n   184→### Agent Model Used\n   185→\n   186→Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n   187→\n   188→### Debug Log References\n   189→\n   190→### Completion Notes List\n   191→\n   192→### Change Log\n   193→\n   194→- 2026-03-25: Story created with 9 ACs (2 from epic, 7 derived from architecture, testing, and code analysis). Full implementation guidance with file locations, line budgets, and anti-patterns. Status set to ready-for-dev.\n   195→- 2026-03-25: Implementation complete. All 9 tasks done. 3672 tests pass, build succeeds, run.ts at exactly 300 lines. Status set to review.\n   196→\n   197→### File List\n   198→\n   199→- `src/commands/run.ts` — Added Docker pre-check (step 1c) and orphan cleanup (step 1d) to pre-flight. +2 imports, +13 lines logic. 300 lines total.\n   200→- `src/modules/infra/container-cleanup.ts` — Added `'codeharness-verify-'` to STALE_PATTERNS. 83 lines.\n   201→- `src/lib/docker/cleanup.ts` — Updated stub to delegate to infra module's cleanupContainers(). 26 lines.\n   202→- `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` — Added 4 tests for Docker pre-check and cleanup behavior. 947 lines.\n   203→- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/container-cleanup.test.ts` — Added verify-pattern test. 173 lines.\n   204→- `src/lib/docker/__tests__/cleanup.test.ts` — Rewrote to test delegation to infra module. 50 lines.\n   205→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01NrzDLhF9NNDZQrr8WemqQC","session_id":"174e0897-5fbc-4ae0-bbc6-8b881d5c7525","uuid":"eeffd3d9-7371-4363-a714-b49005bc67f2","timestamp":"2026-03-24T22:52:04.224Z"}
